      "label": "sequence"
    },
    {
      "type": "group",
      "id": "rx04d5e6f7g8h9i0",
      "x": -780,
      "y": 1930,
      "width": 540,
      "height": 150,
      "color": "4",
      "label": "parallel (nested)"
    },
    {
      "type": "group",
      "id": "grp_pipeline_ts01",
      "x": -560,
      "y": -120,
      "width": 900,
      "height": 500,
      "color": "6",
      "label": "PIPELINE DEFINITION"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "s3c4d5e6f7g8h9i0",
      "x": -340,
      "y": 540,
      "width": 480,
      "height": 460,
      "color": "2",
      "text": "## Prompt Step (atomic unit)\n\n```ts\ninterface Step {\n  kind: \"prompt\";\n  label?: string;\n  model?: { provider: string; id: string };\n  tools?: string[];\n  temperature?: number;\n  systemPrompt?: string;\n  skills?: string[];\n  prompt: string;   // supports $INPUT, $ORIGINAL\n  gate?: Gate;\n  onFail?: OnFail;\n  transform?: Transform;\n}\n```"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "pip01a2b3c4d5e6f7",
      "x": -540,
      "y": -80,
      "width": 400,
      "height": 440,
      "color": "6",
      "text": "## pipeline.ts\n\nExport any `Runnable` -- fully type-safe\n\n```ts\nimport type { Runnable } from \"./captain.js\";\nimport { nonempty, llmScore, joinSections } from \"./captain.js\";\n\nexport const pipeline: Runnable = {\n  kind: \"parallel\",\n  steps: [researchStep, analyzeStep],\n  merge: joinSections(\"---\"),\n  gate: nonempty(),\n  onFail: { action: \"retry\", max: 2 },\n};\n```\n\nLoad with: `captain load <path>`"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "pre01b2c3d4e5f6g7",
      "x": -100,
      "y": -80,
      "width": 400,
      "height": 440,
      "color": "6",
      "text": "## Built-in Presets\n\nImport from `\"./captain.js\"`\n\n**Gates**\n`nonempty()` -- output is not empty\n`json()` -- output is valid JSON\n`contains(str)` -- output includes string\n`llmScore(prompt, min)` -- LLM scores output\n\n**OnFail**\n`{ action: \"retry\", max? }`\n`{ action: \"skip\" }`\n`{ action: \"abort\" }`\n`{ action: \"fallback\", step }`\n\n**Merge** (`MergeFn` presets)\n`joinSections(sep)`, `keepFirst`, `keepLast`\n`vote`, `interleave`"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "p8h9i0j1k2l3m4n5",
      "x": -780,
      "y": 1350,
      "width": 150,
      "height": 55,
      "color": "2",
      "text": "**step: plan**"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "d0j1k2l3m4n5o6p7",
      "x": -780,
      "y": 1420,
      "width": 450,
      "height": 300,
      "text": "Steps run in order\nOutput chains via `$INPUT`\n\n```ts\nconst seq: Sequential = {\n  kind: \"sequential\",\n  steps: [planStep, buildStep],\n};\n```"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "b9i0j1k2l3m4n5o6",
      "x": -610,
      "y": 1350,
      "width": 150,
      "height": 55,
      "color": "2",
      "text": "**step: build**"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "e5o6p7q8r9s0t1u2",
      "x": 280,
      "y": 1350,
      "width": 450,
      "height": 55,
      "color": "2",
      "text": "**search** + **lint** + **typecheck**"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "h6p7q8r9s0t1u2v3",
      "x": 280,
      "y": 1420,
      "width": 450,
      "height": 310,
      "text": "Run **different** steps concurrently\nEach has its own prompt & gate\n\n```ts\nconst par: Parallel = {\n  kind: \"parallel\",\n  steps: [search, lint, typecheck],\n  merge: joinSections(\"---\"),\n};\n```"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "g5e6f7g8h9i0j1k2",
      "x": 420,
      "y": 390,
      "width": 520,
      "height": 590,
      "text": "## Gate & Function Types\n\n```ts\n// Gate -- pure function\ntype Gate = (params: {\n  output: string;\n  ctx?: GateCtx;\n}) => true | string | Promise<true | string>;\n// true = pass, string = failure reason\n\n// OnFail -- plain object or function\ntype OnFail =\n  | { action: \"retry\"; max?: number }\n  | { action: \"skip\" | \"abort\" }\n  | { action: \"fallback\"; step: Step };\n\n// Transform -- pure function\ntype Transform = (params: {\n  output: string;\n  original: string;\n}) => string | Promise<string>;\n\n// MergeFn -- pure function\ntype MergeFn = (\n  outputs: string[],\n  ctx: MergeCtx,\n) => string | Promise<string>;\n```"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "ty01a2b3c4d5e6f7",
      "x": -1125,
      "y": 400,
      "width": 420,
      "height": 700,
      "color": "2",
      "text": "## Core Type Union\n\n```ts\n// Every composable unit is a Runnable\ntype Runnable =\n  | Step\n  | Sequential\n  | Parallel;\n\ninterface Sequential {\n  kind: \"sequential\";\n  steps: Runnable[];\n  gate?: Gate;\n  onFail?: OnFail;\n  transform?: Transform;\n}\n\ninterface Parallel {\n  kind: \"parallel\";\n  steps: Runnable[];\n  merge: MergeFn;\n  gate?: Gate;\n  onFail?: OnFail;\n  transform?: Transform;\n}\n```"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "t1a2b3c4d5e6f7g8",
      "x": -340,
      "y": -460,
      "width": 500,
      "height": 130,
      "color": "1",
      "text": "# Agent Orchestration\n\nComposable steps \u2192 groups \u2192 pipelines\n**Fully type-safe \u2014 TypeScript all the way down**"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "rx12l3m4n5o6p7q8",
      "x": 40,
      "y": 2240,
      "width": 700,
      "height": 320,
      "color": "1",
      "text": "## Recursive Composition\n\n```ts\n// Any slot accepts Runnable (Step | Sequential | Parallel)\nconst pipeline: Parallel = {\n  kind: \"parallel\",\n  steps: [\n    innerParallel, // { kind: \"parallel\", steps: [search, analyze] }\n    { kind: \"sequential\", steps: [planStep, reviewStep] },\n  ],\n  merge: joinSections(\"---\"),\n};\n```"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "rx02b3c4d5e6f7g8",
      "x": -380,
      "y": 2440,
      "width": 400,
      "height": 100,
      "text": "Any slot that accepts a **step**\nalso accepts **sequential**\nor **parallel** -- infinite nesting"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "rx06f7g8h9i0j1k2",
      "x": -500,
      "y": 1955,
      "width": 240,
      "height": 45,
      "color": "2",
      "text": "**step: analyze**"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "rx05e6f7g8h9i0j1",
      "x": -760,
      "y": 1955,
      "width": 240,
      "height": 45,
      "color": "2",
      "text": "**step: search**"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "rx07g8h9i0j1k2l3",
      "x": -760,
      "y": 2010,
      "width": 500,
      "height": 50,
      "text": "\u2191 2 different steps run concurrently"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "cg01a2b3c4d5e6f7",
      "x": -1660,
      "y": 900,
      "width": 420,
      "height": 340,
      "color": "3",
      "text": "## Composition Gates\n\nGates validate the **scope** they are on:\n- `sequential.gate` -- validates final chained output\n- `parallel.gate` -- validates merged output\n\n**retry = retry that scope**\nThe topology is the retry boundary.\n\nNo new types -- same `Gate` + `OnFail`,\njust optional on composition nodes."
    }
  ],
